quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  34,32,"Those who were proud shall say to those who were deemed weak (or despised), \"Did we turn you away from the guidance after it had come to you? Nay, you (yourselves) were guilty"
  34,33,"And those who were deemed weak (despised) shall say to those who were proud, \"Nay, it was your scheming night and day when you told us to disbelieve in Allah and to set up rivals with Him.\" And they shall declare repentance when they see the pen"
  34,34,"And We never sent a Warner to a town but those who led lives in ease in it said, \"We are surely disbelievers in what you are sent with"
  34,35,"And they say, \"We have more wealth and children, and we shall not be punished"
  34,36,"Say, \"Surely my Lord amplifies the means of subsistence for whom He pleases and restricts it (for whom He pleases), but most men know not"
  34,37,"It is not your wealth nor your children which bring you near Us in station, but whoever believes and does good, these it is for whom is a double reward for what they do, and they shall be secure in the highest places"
  34,38,"And as for those who strive in opposing Our revelations, they shall be brought to the chastisement"
  34,39,"Say, \"Surely my Lord amplifies the means of subsistence for whom He pleases of His servants and restricts them (for whom He wills). And whatever you spend, He replaces it, and He is the best of Providers"